mage/upload/t_td-list-m-2/f_auto/main/2018/12/thediplomat-international-2690941_1280.jpg 438w" data-src="https://res.cloudinary.com/thediplomat/image/upload/t_td-list-s-1/f_auto/main/2018/12/thediplomat-international-2690941_1280.jpg" src="https://thediplomat.com/wp-content/themes/td_theme_v3/assets/img-paceholder.svg" loading="lazy"></figure><h5>November 14, 2019</h5><h4>What’s Next for Cambodia’s Opposition Politics?</h4><h6>By <span>David Hutt</span></h6><div>After a big week for the country’s opposition, a look at what may lie ahead for it as well as Cambodian politics more generally.</div></a><a href="/2019/10/how-close-is-rcep-to-reality/" class="td-post d-4"><figure class="td-img td-post__img td-post__img--right-s"><img alt="How Close Is RCEP to Reality?" title="How Close Is RCEP to Reality?" data-sizes="(max-width: 319px) 100vw, (max-width: 752px) 138px, 219px" data-srcset="https://res.cloudinary.com/thediplomat/image/upload/t_td-list-s-1/f_auto/main/2018/10/thediplomat-ap_17142144182939.jpg 138w, https://res.cloudinary.com/thediplomat/image/upload/t_td-list-s-2/f_auto/main/2018/10/thediplomat-ap_17142144182939.jpg 276w, https://res.cloudinary.com/thediplomat/image/upload/t_td-list-m-1/f_auto/main/2018/10/thediplomat-ap_17142144182939.jpg 219w, https://res.cloudinary.com/thediplomat/image/upload/t_td-list-m-2/f_auto/main/2018/10/thediplomat-ap_17142144182939.jpg 438w" data-src="https://res.cloudinary.com/thediplomat/image/upload/t_td-list-s-1/f_auto/main/2018/10/thediplomat-ap_17142144182939.jpg" src="https://thediplomat.com/wp-content/themes/td_theme_v3/assets/img-paceholder.svg" loading="lazy"></figure><h5>October 16, 2019</h5><h4>How Close Is RCEP to Reality?</h4><h6>By <span>Luke Hunt</span></h6><div>While progress continues to be touted, challenges remain to be addressed.</div></a><div class="td-vertical-line td-1"></div><div class="td-vertical-line td-2"></div><div class="td-vertical-line td-3"></div></div></div></div><aside class="td-box td-2"><header